data.content:
noun
plural ~ chains
[count] :a series of types of living things in which each one uses the next lower member of the series as a source of food - usually used with the
Sharks eat fish that are lower in the food chain.
animals that are at the top/bottom of the food chain - often used figuratively
directors and producers at the top of the Hollywood food chain [=very powerful and successful directors and producers]
the corporate food chain
dây chuyền thức ăn (trong giới sinh vật)
